A businessman, Mustapha Umar,  on Tuesday appeared in a Life Camp Magistrates’ Court, Abuja, for allegedly defrauding a man of N3. 9 million. Umar, who resides at  Sabon Lugbe, Abuja, is charged with two counts of criminal breach of trust and cheating. He, however, pleaded not guilty. The prosecution counsel, Peter Ejike,  told the court that  the complainant, one Muhammed Abdullahi of Nasarawa Avenue, War College Quarters, Gwarimpa, Abuja, reported the matter at Life Camp Police Station on June 1. Ejike alleged that the defendant on March 19, bought frozen chicken worth N4.3 million from the complainant The prosecutor further alleged that  the defendant made some payment and dishonestly  refused to pay the balance of N3. 9 million. He said that the offence contravened the provisions of  Sections 312 and  322 of the Penal Code. The Magistrate, Chinyere Nwecheonwe, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N500,000 with one surety in like sum. She adjourned the case until Aug. 31, for hearing. (NAN) 